# BimRoss employee roster (Slack / personality bundles)

## Intent

Multiple first-name **employees** (see **`personas/employees.txt`**) can run in Slack as separate apps. Each **`{name}-personality.md`** bundle should include a **`{name}-sibling-agents.mdc`** rule so the model **knows who else exists**, **what they’re for**, and may **@mention** them in-thread for a purposeful handoff (Slack notifies the other bot).

**Strategic questions** (“what should we work on at BimRoss,” “what’s next,” priorities): every employee bundle already prepends **`bimross-company.mdc`**—use it as the shared backbone (operating filters, stack, product shape, cursor-rules as doctrine). Differentiate answers by **persona** (Alex / Tim / Ross / Garth), not by inventing different “company facts.”

## Required shape

1. **One file per employee:** `.cursor/rules/{name}-sibling-agents.mdc` (not `*-trigger` / `*-factory`—those stay Cursor-only in compact bundles).
2. **Content:** Short roster table: every **other** current employee, one-line role, when to @mention.
3. **Slack text:** Instruct to use **`@DisplayName`** matching each Slack app’s **display name** (e.g. `Alex`, `Tim`, `Ross`, `Garth` from **`slack-factory/manifests/*/app-manifest.json`**).
4. **Spam guard:** Always say mentions are **optional** and **sparing**—not every message.

## Canonical bot user IDs (GitOps)

Runtime `U…` IDs for Ross / Tim / Alex / Garth live in **`employee-factory`** + **`rancher-admin`**—not in `slack-factory` manifests. When changing or debugging multi-agent / `<@U…>` behavior, follow **`employee-factory-slack-squad-ids.mdc`** and **`employee-factory/docs/slack-squad-ids.md`**.

## When adding a **new** employee

1. Add `{new}-sibling-agents.mdc` describing all **existing** peers.
2. **Edit every existing** `{peer}-sibling-agents.mdc` to add a row for the new agent (roster is symmetric).
3. Add `{new}` to **`personas/employees.txt`** (separate step from this file—see **`docs/employee-agents.md`**).
4. Add an index line to **`{name}-trigger.mdc`** under a **BimRoss Slack** / **Peers** row pointing at `*-sibling-agents`.
5. Run **`./scripts/sync-employee-personality.sh --all`** and commit **`*.mdc`** + **`.cursor/personas/*-personality.md`** together (**`sync-employee-personality.mdc`**).

## Current roster (maintain in sibling files when this changes)

`alex`, `tim`, `ross`, `garth` — update this list when employees change.
